<h2>Frequent Asthma Causes</h2>
<p>Food sensitivities can cause asthma in 75% of children and 40% of adults. Dairy, eggs, wheat, gluten, citrus, peanuts, and chocolate are some of the most common allergens and asthma causes, although any food can be a potential irritant. Unfortunately, hidden allergies and food sensitivities are ignored by the conventional medical community, and most people are unaware of this type of allergy.</p>
<h2>Natural Holistic Asthma Treatments</h2>
<p>Almost always an elimination diet is the most powerful tool in determining and treating food sensitivities. Intravenous Magnesium or <a href="/treatments/myers-cocktail/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><u>Myers’ cocktail</u></a> is a great tool in reducing muscle spasm in the airway of the lungs. Glutathione nebulizer is also prescribed to heal the lining of the bronchioles and open up the airway. Omega 3 fish oils in high doses are used to reduce inflammation in the lungs. High dose <a href="/treatments/vitamin-c-iv/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><u>IV vitamin C</u></a>, B6, B12, Selenium and molybdenum are also very important in the treatment of asthma.</p>
